value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which a dividing cell at the growith end of a hypha has a septum in an abnormal location. Normally, the septum forms in the cytosol-enriched portion of the cell, displaced slightly off-center toward the portion of the cell occupied by the vacuole.
A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form linear element that are shorter than normal.
A cellular process phenotype in which macroautophagy does not occur when the cell is subject to leucine starvation.

label.value: abnormal H3-H4 dimer loading onto DNA

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the ATP hydrolysis-dependent activity that loads H3-H4 histone dimers onto DNA is abnormal.

label.value: abolished H3-H4 dimer loading onto DNA

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the ATP hydrolysis-dependent activity that loads H3-H4 histone dimers onto DNA is absent.
A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a endodeoxyribonuclease activator is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a endodeoxyribonuclease activator is decreased.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of valproic acid than normal.
A physical cellular phenotype in which the amount, distribution, and morphology of cytoplasmic microtubules is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal cytoplasmic microtubules during cellular response to pheromone

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the amount, distribution, and morphology of cytoplasmic microtubules is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to a pheromone.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of CMG replicative helicase activity, the 3'-5' DNA helicase activity that unwinds DNA during nuclear DNA replication, is decreased.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to stavudine. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of stavudine that allows wild type cells to grow.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing stavudine.

label.value: increased rate of mitotic DNA replication elongation during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of DNA strand elongation involved in mitotic nuclear DNA replication is increased during a cellular response to hydroxyurea.

label.value: normal protein localization to protein aggregate center

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to protein aggregate centers is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Protein aggregate centers are composed of chaperones and misfolded proteins, and are reversibly formed in the nucleus and cytosol to shield thermosensitive proteins from degradation until conditions allow disaggregation and refolding.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of polyphosphate measured in a cell (total or free) is higher than normal.
A physical cellular phenotype in which a cell has a nucleus in an abnormal location during G0 phase. The normal location is at the midpoint of the long axis of the cell.

label.value: decreased protein ubiquitination during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of ubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is decreased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of polyphosphate measured in a cell is too low to detect.
A physical cellular phenotype in which vacuoles are larger than normal.
A physical cellular phenotype in which vacuoles are larger than normal in G0 phase.
A biological process phenotype in which any aspect of quorum sensing is abnormal.
A biological process phenotype in which a response to quorum sensing molecules (QSMs) is decreased. The amount of QSMs may be normal.

label.value: decreased protein level during cellular response to amino acid starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to amino acid starvation is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein level during cellular response to leucine starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to leucine starvation is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin contractile ring organization is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The process results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the actomyosin contractile ring.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin contractile ring maturation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: premature protein localization to cell division site

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the site of cell division begins earlier than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: narrow protein radial density distribution in medial cortical node during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein located in the medial cortical nodes occupies an area with a smaller radius than normal during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. The nodes are "precursor" nodes that exist before the contractile ring is formed.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: narrow protein radial density distribution in medial cortical node during mitotic anaphase B

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein located in the medial cortical nodes occupies an area with a smaller radius than normal during anaphase B of mitosis. The nodes are "ring" nodes, observed when the contractile ring is constricting.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of protein localization to medial cortical node

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the medial cortical nodes begins later than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal nucleosome positioning at protein-coding gene

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome positioning is abnormal in regions containing protein-coding genes.

label.value: protein displaced from 5' end to 3' end of RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin along the length of genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase II is altered such that more of the protein is present at the 3' end, and less at the 5' end, than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which histone binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant occurs to a greater extent than normal. The affected protein may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is greater than normal at subtelomeric regions. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is lower than normal at subtelomeric regions. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of peptide alpha-N-acetyltransferase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of peptide alpha-N-acetyltransferase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of peptide alpha-N-acetyltransferase activity is increased.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of peptide alpha-N-acetyltransferase activity is decreased.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of peptide alpha-N-acetyltransferase activity is absent.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome positioning in centromeric regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Nucleosome positioning is the ordering of successions of nucleosomes into regular arrays so that nucleosomes are positioned at defined distances from one another.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 monomethylation at centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the monomethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in centromere inner repeat regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased rate of RNA catabolic process during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of an RNA catabolic process is increased.

label.value: short meiotic spindle during anaphase I

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the spindle is shorter than normal during anaphase of meiosis I.
A physical cellular phenotype in which the meiotic spindle is longer than normal during meiosis I.

A cellular process phenotype in which microtubules self-assemble into a spindle without the participation of the spindle pole body (SPB) during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions. This phenotype is observed in the absence of both bouquet formation and meiotic SPB insertion into the nuclear envelope.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'meiotic spindle pole body detached from nucleus' (FYPO:0006365).

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which microtubules self-assemble into a spindle without the participation of the spindle pole body (SPB) during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'meiotic spindle pole body detached from nucleus' (FYPO:0006365).

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which microtubules self-assemble into a spindle without the participation of the spindle pole body (SPB) during the second meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'meiotic spindle pole body detached from nucleus' (FYPO:0006365).

label.value: abolished spindle assembly during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which spindle assembly does not occur during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'meiotic spindle pole body detached from nucleus' (FYPO:0006365).
